  "body": "### Description\r\nKintsugi v2 spec indicates we should merge the duties of engine_getPayload with engine_forkChoiceUpdated.  See https://hackmd.io/@n0ble/kintsugi-spec#Engine-API\r\n\r\nRather than there being a different endpoint to signify that an execution client should start producing a block at slot n, the message is included with the forkChoiceUpdated call for slot n-1.\r\n\r\nAlso, add `safeBlockHash` to ExecutionForkchoiceUpdatedParameter.  The v2 spec dictates we ignore this value for now, the consensus clients are not implementing safeBlockHash algo for this iteration.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* implemented in `merge-branch`\r\n* remove engine_preparePayload\r\n* rename engine_forkChoiceUpdated to engine_forkChoiceUpdatedV1\r\n* add ExecutionForkChoiceUpdatedParameter \r\n",
